The paper deals with sub-Nyquist sampling and reconstruction of a continuous-time Gaussian stationary process, which falls under the domains of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses optimization of pre-sampling filters, which is related to machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper unifies two important concepts in information theory, namely the Shannon-Whittaker-Kotelnikov sampling theorem and Shannon rate-distortion theory, which could potentially fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
